args: Ahhh, time flies when you're having fun!\nThose old fishermen's stories are\nsurprisingly wild, huh?
I found them most enlightening. It is wise\nto have those who know the sea best\ncontribute that knowledge to its defense.
Ha ha! I hang out with them pretty often,\nso I'd heard a lot of it before, but I guess\nit's all new to you, huh?
Now that we've put a bow on today, what\ndo you want to do tomorrow? Any ideas?
Anywhere you wanna go, just let me know!\nI'll make it happen.
A most generous offer, my friend. Sadly,\nI board a ship tomorrow afternoon to sail\nback home, so I cannot partake.
Huh. No kidding? You sail back tomorrow...\nWait, TOMORROW?! Seriously?
I'm afraid so. Our time together has been\nso unrelentingly entertaining, I fear I never\nfound the right moment to mention it.
I wish we had longer, and I do apologize\nfor not telling you earlier. But I'm glad—
NO! I don't want to think about saying\ngoodbye!
I don't want to watch some dumb boat\ncome and take you away. I'm not...\nI won't come and see you off! I won't!
Ah—! Setta! Please, wait... Oh dear.
How regrettable that we should have to\npart like this.
The ship is ready to sail, Lord Ieyasu. You\nare welcome to board and await departure\nfrom the comfort of your cabin.
I suppose it's already that time. *sigh*
COME ON! Rescue formation, everyone!\nIf we don't hurry, we'll lose Setta!
Pardon my interruption, but what's\nhappened? Is Setta all right?
Oh, Ieyasu! Bad news, I'm afraid. Setta\nwent into a dangerous cave by himself.
It's smack in the middle of an infamously\nrough patch of sea. Plus, it's nearly high\ntide. The water's only getting rougher.
What?! Please, allow me to assist in his\nrescue!
Lord Ieyasu, what are you saying?!\nI cannot allow an envoy from Hinomoto\nto engage in such a dangerous venture!
I implore you, leave this to the experts!
I will not, for I expect I bear some\nresponsibility for Setta's actions.
Besides, he has been a true friend during\nmy entire stay here. I will not stand idly by\nwhile he is in peril!
I beg you to understand my position.\nPlease, permit me to make this right!
*sigh* Very well. You have been a difficult\nguest to handle from the very start, but I\ncannot ignore so sincere a plea.
I suppose this must be the oft-touted\nhonor of a Hinomotoan warrior on display.\nIn which case... You there. Lifeguard!
On behalf of my master, the lord of this\nland, offer whatever assistance you can to\nLord Ieyasu in this matter.
Understood, sir. Ieyasu, you take the\nseacutter! We'll be right behind you\non our rescue boats.
My thanks! I will not forget this kindness.
*cough* *gasp* You've gotta be kidding\nme... What's with these waves?!
How am I supposed to get back through\nthis? And after I finally found what I was\nafter, too.
I bet Ieyasu's mad I didn't show up to\nsee him off.
Ugh, what am I doing? Am I really gonna...\ndie here? Without getting to say I'm sorry?
Wait, Ieyasu?! What are you doing HERE?!\nWeren't you headed back home today?
I couldn't very well leave you in danger.\nI've come to help!
I didn't mean for any of this. I've caused\nyou nothing but trouble. I'm so, so sorry!
You've done nothing of the sort, Setta.\nI'm just relieved you're safe. But come,\nquickly. It will be high tide soon.
The cave is beginning to flood with\nseawater!
The waves have gotten too high.\nWe'll drown if we stay here! But...
Blast. It's too dangerous to go out there\nwith the sea this rough. Is there anything\nyou can do, Marishiten?
Sorry. Even with my strength, carrying the\ntwo of you through those waves is a losing\nprospect. We'd just be swept away.
No... What are we supposed to do?!
